race.comment: FLAGSHIP (2) will find this much easier than recent races and he's a course and distance winner in the past. He was in strong form prior to his run last start in a CL3 at Belmont, but this looks a great opportunity for him to bounce back. Cheung's claim comes in handy and he looks the one to beat. ZAC LUVS TO FLY (4) just felt the pinch late first-up over 1100m here, beaten 0.8L. He had to do some work from the wide draw and was coming into that event without a trial. Should have come on from that performance and he'll be hard to gun down. PRETTY DEVINE (1) drops right back from Saturday grade where she was well beaten last time out at Ascot. She was a winner of this track and trip first-up, and that was in this grade as well. Carries more weight today, but she's well placed and can bounce back to form. ENSIGN PULVER (5) is not out of this first-up. DADIRRA (6) can feature in the finish off a short break.
